Anyway
He looks ten years older than when
] last
saw him and certainly is far from robuste
He said the Generalissimo
in a talkative mood once told him "you nordie people are not like us latins
you have on election campaign during the course of which each aspirant
calls the other every kind of a crook and imbicile but when one wins they
shake hands and thats the end of it.
However with us Latins the men who
gets
licked innediately starts plotting to over throw the government and
so often succeeds that the crowd which
wins steals everything in sight know-
ing that they wont be around very long."
Trujillo has been running the show
in San Domingo for 25 years or more and has
really done a job. They have
more schools per capita then we,
more hospital beds, education is cumpul-
sory to 60,
the country has no debt, every little town has good and adequate
water supply, fine roads run everywhere and Cided Trujillo is the cleanest
city in the world.
We left Sen Domingo on the worning of the 24th flew over count-
less islands surrounded by that crystal clear water so characteristic of
section with miles and hiles of beaches over Eluthers and Nesau on in
to Patrick Air Force Base just south of Cocoa, Florida.
ladies
were entertained by their local counterparts while the men all of whon had
been cleared for "top secret" received a briefing
- very well
done - and
then went to Cape Canaverel.
They are so particular
about that test range
that I wont say anything except that it was most interesting.
PAA is play-
ing an importent part which the Commanding General very graciously acknow
ledged.
The main party left around seven P.M. for New York while
the Gledhills and Bixbys flew in Wilbur Morrison's DC3 to Mieni and then
Ma and I
continued on
alone in the DC3 to Port Myers.
One
sad note.
At Santiago, Chili Mrs.
Bob Fleming wife of
the Chairmen
of
the Riggs Bank in Washington who has been on many
of these
trips with us ga had a stroke from which she never
regained conciouness.
Bob
stayed
with her in Santiago and brought her body
back to Washington.
The
captain of our
ship was an old
Pacifie pilot who you
may remember Capt.
Purser
Vinal.
We had two most attractive
Stewardesses, a
who was very
good.
A First Officer and & flight engineer completed
the crew.
The Directors were the Triypes, Leslies, Gledhills, Mc Kees
Ishe is a new wife who calls herself an Hawaiian
but she looks
Chinese)
Lewis's,
Howards,
Ingalls, Chandlers, Manils, Henry Friendly and Adniral
McDonnel
the
latter
two without wives.
After a trip around the world in January and around
Ancrica in Febuary I would like to
confine ny further
50.
travels to the
Kinsey boat line between Captiva and the mainland but will have to make
some more trips to N.Y.
Lots of love
